OL,3,CHome Office has chance to end 'failed'
OL,4,Casylum accommodation system, MPs say
OL,6,FThe chairwoman of the Home Affairs
OL,7,FCommittee, Dame Karen Bradley, said:
OL,8,F"The Government needs to get a grip on
OL,9,Fthe asylum accommodation system in
OL,10,Forder to bring costs down and hold
OL,11,Fproviders to account for poor
OL,12,Fperformance.
OL,14,F"While reducing hotel use is rightly a
OL,15,FGovernment priority, there will always
OL,16,Fbe a need for flexibility within the
OL,17,Fsystem, and the Home Office risks
OL,18,Fboxing itself in by making
OL,19,Fundeliverable promises to appeal to
OL,20,Fpopular sentiment. It shouldn't set
OL,21,Fitself up for more failure.
OL,26,@pD@AOUvD@AOU
