OL,3,CHome Office has chance to end 'failed'
OL,4,Casylum accommodation system, MPs say
OL,6,FThis includes no fines for failures at
OL,7,Fhotels and the large accommodation
OL,8,Fsites at Napier Barracks and
OL,9,FWethersfield, despite hotels making up
OL,10,Fmore than 75% of spending on asylum
OL,11,Faccommodation.
OL,13,FFurthermore, excess profits from
OL,14,Fproviders totalling tens of millions
OL,15,Fof pounds owed to the Home Office are
OL,16,Fyet to be reclaimed by the department.
OL,18,FThe committee said the money should be
OL,19,Fused on public services, "not sitting
OL,20,Fin the bank accounts of private
OL,21,Fbusinesses".
